description: Returns an array of ChannelInfo objects. Each object describes a signaling channel. To retrieve only those channels that satisfy a specific condition, you can specify a ChannelNameCondition.

parameters.name: ChannelNameCondition
parameters.description: Optional: Returns only the channels that satisfy a specific condition. ComparisonOperator (string) --- A comparison operator. Currently, you can only specify the BEGINS_WITH operator, which finds signaling channels whose names begin with a given prefix. ComparisonValue (string) --- A value to compare.

nested_params.name: ComparisonOperator
nested_params.description: A comparison operator. Currently, you can only specify the BEGINS_WITH operator, which finds signaling channels whose names begin with a given prefix.

nested_items.name: ChannelName
nested_items.description: The name of the signaling channel.

nested_items.name: ChannelARN
nested_items.description: The Amazon Resource Name (ARN) of the signaling channel.

nested_items.name: ChannelType
nested_items.description: The type of the signaling channel.

nested_items.name: ChannelStatus
nested_items.description: Current status of the signaling channel.

nested_items.name: CreationTime
nested_items.description: The time at which the signaling channel was created.

nested_items.name: SingleMasterConfiguration
nested_items.description: A structure that contains the configuration for the SINGLE_MASTER channel type.

nested_items.name: MessageTtlSeconds
nested_items.description: The period of time a signaling channel retains undelivered messages before they are discarded.

nested_items.name: Version
nested_items.description: The current version of the signaling channel.

nested_items.name: NextToken
nested_items.description: If the response is truncated, the call returns this element with a token. To get the next batch of streams, use this token in your next request.
